I am not in beta either, but that is exactly the impression I get from all that I have read.  Another way to say it is collection quests when you need to get 20 beetle legs are just random drops like any normal drop, so one person loots each time you kill one and that is it.  For quests where you have to kill Mr. BignBad and bring back his head as proof, everyone who has the quest will be able to loot the head.  I am pretty sure that is correct.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
<br /><table class="tborder" cellpadding="6" cellspacing="1" border="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td class="page">
	
		<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
		<tr valign="bottom">
			<td style="font-size:14pt">Telegareth</td>
			<td class="smallfont" align="right">April 29th, 2004 07:43 AM</td>
		</tr>
		</table>
		
		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>Collection quests are best done solo, since you have to collect like 10 red bandannas or something which drop from normal mobs randomly, and only one red bandanna per mob.  If you are in a group, then it's random drop if you get the quest item.<br />
<br />
Assasination quests are different in that you need to go kill "Mr. X" and bring back proof that you killed him.  In this case, Mr. X will drop however many items of proof are needed for those in the party that have the quest.<br />
<br />
One thing to note about collection quests and the loot rules (usually set to round robin).  If you are in a group of players killing Murloc's for their fins or something, and one person gathers all their items before the rest, that doesn't mean that the mobs he is able to loot won't drop the quest items.  After he is done looting everything he sees on the corpse, those that still require that item will be able to loot it.  Say i'm in a group with two others killing Murlocs.  I need 8 fins to finish, the mage needs 4, and the druid needs 1.  I get to loot every third mob which may or may not have a fin, same with the others in the group.  After the druid loots his last fin, he won't see any more fins drop on mobs, however the mage and myself will be able to loot a fin off the druid's mob if it has one.  It's best to keep an eye on your party-members corpses after they finish looting, their might be a quest item you need on it that they don't and won't see.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
